                "invention-title": [
                    "Method for discovering hidden fracture structure by using natural hydrogen in soil",
                    "一种利用土壤天然氢发现隐伏断裂构造的方法"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention relates to the technical field of geological exploration, in particular to a method for discovering a concealed fracture structure by using natural hydrogen in soil. According to the method, any measuring line is arranged for an area to be explored through concealed fracture exploration measuring line layout, it is assumed that the measuring line is perpendicular to the trend of concealed fracture, and then the in-situ hydrogen concentration of one measuring point is collected and analyzed through a soil hydrogen collection and analysis method; and finally, determining the hydrogen concentration abnormity through the lower limit of the hydrogen concentration abnormal value, after the hydrogen concentration abnormity is obtained, inferring the top position of the hidden fracture through the position of the profile hydrogen concentration peak value, determining a hydrogen migration channel, and on the basis, obtaining the real geologic structure distribution characteristics of the hidden fracture layer through verification. The exploration method is slightly influenced by field conditions and human factors, meanwhile, the exploration cost is low, the natural hydrogen migration channel can be determined, and a favorable area is provided for further exploration of the natural hydrogen reservoir."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明涉及地质勘察技术领域，特别涉及一种利用土壤天然氢发现隐伏断裂构造的方法。本发明通过隐伏断裂勘查测线布设为所要勘查的区域进行任意测线布置，并假定该测线垂直于隐伏断裂的走向，然后通过土壤氢气采集分析方法采集分析其中一个测量点的原位氢气浓度，最后便可以通过氢气浓度异常值下限确定氢气浓度异常，在得到氢气浓度异常后，通过剖面氢气浓度峰值的位置推断出隐伏断裂顶部位置，确定氢气运移通道，以此为基础，通过验证得到真实的隐伏断裂层的地质结构分布特征，该勘查方法受野外条件和人为影响较小，同时勘查成本较低，而且还可帮助确定天然氢运移通道，为进一步勘查天然氢气藏提供有利区域。"
                }
            ]
